          <y:NodeLabel alignment="left" autoSizePolicy="content" fontFamily="Dialog" fontSize="12" fontStyle="plain" hasBackgroundColor="false" hasLineColor="false" height="159.4609375" horizontalTextPosition="center" iconTextGap="4" modelName="internal" modelPosition="t" textColor="#000000" verticalTextPosition="bottom" visible="true" width="373.31640625" x="5.051985751381892" xml:space="preserve" y="4.0">Maps to USDM entity StudyDefinitionDocument,
initially only for the protocol document.
Attribute values and relationship to document version status
will be made during the study release/lock process. Via the
study versioning/audit trail previous values can be identified
and this can be used to map data to the USDM
StudyDefinitionDocumentVersion entity.
Later we will add data structures for USDM GovernanceDate
entity, as these dates are done by signing documents in CTMS
document systems it must be done in a way where these can
be done by data integration after the study definition is locked.</y:NodeLabel>
          <y:Shape type="rectangle"/>
        </y:ShapeNode>
      </data>
    </node>
